textBeforeTable: The State of Wisconsin requires the 30 hours of classroom, 6 hours behind the wheel and 6 hours of car observation. To register for one of those classes, please click below. For more class registration options, please click on the "register now" tab at the top of the page. All of our classes will be held at the Logemann Community Center, 6100 W. Mequon Rd. Mequon, WI 53092 Total Cost $395 (includes classroom and behind the wheel) Pay online with PayPal or pay by mail We offer the DMV knowledge and signs test (temps test) to our students under 18 years of age. All classes are taught by Wisconsin Department of Transportation Certified Instructors You only need to be 14 1/2 years old to sign up for the classroom portion of driver's ed! "educating teens to make safe driving choices" (262) 993-7867 welcome to just drive mequon
